  "body": "### Describe the feature\n\nFor simple repro, see my verification script [here](https://github.com/pcaversaccio/createx/blob/4305ac2125f8b55e58793bf36f12d5f99e213f43/scripts/deploy.ts#L7-L20):\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nasync function main() {\r\n  const contract = await ethers.deployContract(\"CreateX\");\r\n\r\n  await contract.waitForDeployment();\r\n  const contractAddress = await contract.getAddress();\r\n\r\n  console.log(\"CreateX deployed to:\", contractAddress);\r\n\r\n  await delay(30000); // Wait for 30 seconds before verifying the contract\r\n\r\n  await hre.run(\"verify:verify\", {\r\n    address: contractAddress,\r\n  });\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nand Sourcify is enabled [here](https://github.com/pcaversaccio/createx/blob/4305ac2125f8b55e58793bf36f12d5f99e213f43/hardhat.config.ts#L459-L462):\r\n```ts\r\n  sourcify: {\r\n    // Enable Sourcify verification by default\r\n    enabled: true,\r\n  },\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf you would manually verify a contract, it looks as intended:\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/assets/25297591/25b27a47-6256-4339-8e79-d666ea078208)\r\n\r\nHowever, using it programmatically doesn't verify it on Sourcify:\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/assets/25297591/b0730189-d88e-4fd3-9919-993523ab8a57)\r\n\r\nLet me know if you can repro as well.\n\n### Search terms\n\nsourcify",
